"{\"continue\":{\"rvcontinue\":\"20161222111701|756160961\",\"continue\":\"||\"},\"warnings\":{\"main\":{\"*\":\"Subscribe to the mediawiki-api-announce mailing list at <https://lists.wikimedia.org/mailman/listinfo/mediawiki-api-announce> for notice of API deprecations and breaking changes. Use [[Special:ApiFeatureUsage]] to see usage of deprecated features by your application.\"},\"revisions\":{\"*\":\"Because \\\"rvslots\\\" was not specified, a legacy format has been used for the output. This format is deprecated, and in the future the new format will always be used.\"}},\"query\":{\"normalized\":[{\"from\":\"Troy_Balderson\",\"to\":\"Troy Balderson\"}],\"pages\":{\"25486013\":{\"pageid\":25486013,\"ns\":0,\"title\":\"Troy Balderson\",\"revisions\":[{\"timestamp\":\"2016-12-25T20:55:02Z\",\"contentformat\":\"text/x-wiki\",\"contentmodel\":\"wikitext\",\"*\":\"{{Infobox State Representative\\n| name=Troy Balderson\\n| image name=\\n| state_senate=Ohio\\n| state=Ohio\\n| district=20th\\n| term_start=July 13, 2011\\n| preceded=[[Jimmy Stewart (politician)|Jimmy Stewart]]\\n| succeeded=Incumbent\\n| state_house2=Ohio\\n| state2=Ohio\\n| district2=94th\\n| term2=January 5, 2009 \\u2013 July 13, 2011\\n| preceded2=[[Jim Aslanides]]\\n| succeeded2=[[Brian Hill (Ohio politician)|Brian Hill]]\\n| birth_date={{Birth date and age|1962|01|16}}<ref name=\\\"votesmart\\\" />\\n| birth_place=[[Zanesville, Ohio]],<ref name=\\\"votesmart\\\" /> [[United States|U.S.]]\\n| spouse= Angela Balderson (Divorced)\\n| alma_mater= Zanesville High School\\n| profession=Farmer, and Automotive dealer<ref name=\\\"votesmart\\\" />\\n| residence= [[Zanesville, Ohio]], [[United States|U.S.]]\\n| religion=Christian<ref name=\\\"votesmart\\\" />\\n| party=[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\\n}}\\n\\n'''Troy Balderson''' (born January 16, 1962) is the state senator for the 20th District of the [[Ohio Senate]].  Formerly, he was a member of the [[Ohio House of Representatives]].  He is the chairman of the Senate Energy and Natural Resources Committee.  He is a Republican.\\n\\n==Life and career==\\nBorn and raised in southeastern Ohio, Senator Balderson graduated from Zanesville High School in 1980 and attended both Muskingum College and The Ohio State University. His family has owned and operated a farm in Salem Township for several generations. He also co-owns an automotive dealership that has been in the family for three generations.\\n\\nHaving competed in many races and triathlons, Balderson leads a very active lifestyle. He has one son, Joshua, and remains very involved with community organizations. He resides in Zanesville, Ohio.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ohio Senate|url=http://www.ohiosenate.gov/senate2012/balderson/biography|accessdate=17 December 2012}}</ref>\\nWhen incumbent [[Jim Aslanides]] became term-limited, Balderson sought the Republican nomination for state representative of the 94th Ohio House District. He won the nomination by 67.63% of the vote against Dr. Patrick Johnson.<ref>Brunner, Jennifer [http://www.sos.state.oh.us/SOS/elections/electResultsMain/2008ElectionResults/prohrep.aspx 2008 primary election results] (2008-05-04)</ref> Balderson faced Democrat Jennifer Stewart in the general election. Democrats hoped that Stewart would build on solid party showings from the previous election cycle.<ref>[http://www.ohiodailyblog.com/content/oh-house-94-stewart-d-face-johnston-r-and-balderson-r OH House-94: Stewart (D) to Face Johnston (R) and Balderson (R)]</ref> Having received 54.01%, Balderson was elected to his first term in the Ohio House of Representatives.<ref>Brunner, Jennifer [http://www.sos.state.oh.us/SOS/elections/electResultsMain/2008ElectionResults/ohRep_110408.aspx 2008 general election results] (2008-11-04)</ref>\\n\\nBalderson was unopposed for his seat in the 2010 general election and was awarded a second term.<ref>{{cite web|last=Brunner|first=Jennifer|title=Ohio Secretary of State|url=http://www.sos.state.oh.us/sos/elections/Research/electResultsMain/2010results/20101102ohouse.aspx|accessdate=17 December 2012}}</ref>\\n\\nWhile serving in the Ohio House of Representatives, Balderson was appointed to the powerful House Finance Committee and also presided as Chairman of the Subcommittee on Agriculture and Natural Resources.\\n\\n==Ohio Senate==\\nIn late May 2011, State Senator [[Jimmy Stewart (politician)|Jimmy Stewart]] announced that he planned to resign his seat in the 20th Senate District at the end of the fiscal year.<ref>{{cite news | first = Holly | last = Richards | title = Sen. Jimmy Stewart resigning from Senate seat | date = 2011-05-25 | url = http://www.coshoctontribune.com/article/20110525/NEWS01/105250304 | work = Coshocton Tribune | accessdate = 2011-05-26}}</ref> Stewart continued his service as majority [[floor leader]] until he resigned.<ref>{{cite news | first = Bill | last = Hershey | title = State Sen. Stewart, number three leader, to resign | date = 2011-05-27 | url = http://www.daytondailynews.com/blogs/content/shared-gen/blogs/dayton/ohiopolitics/entries/2011/05/25/state_sen_stewart_number_three.html?cxtype=feedbot | work = [[Dayton Daily News]] | accessdate = 2011-05-26}}</ref>\\n\\nOn July 12, 2011, Senate President [[Tom Niehaus]] announced that Balderson would be appointed to the vacant Senate seat. He was sworn into office on July 13, 2011. On November 6, 2012, Balderson won a full 4-year term in his Senate Seat, defeating Democrat Teresa Scarmack by 59.79% of the vote.<ref>{{cite web|last=Husted|first=John|title=Ohio Secretary of State|url=http://www2.sos.state.oh.us/pls/enrpublic/f?p=212:17:0::NO::P17_OTC:SE|accessdate=17 December 2012}}</ref>\\n\\nBalderson was selected in 2014 as co-chair of a special legislative committee to review Ohio's renewable energy and energy efficiency regulations.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ohio.com/news/break-news/ohio-utility-chief-energy-savings-hard-to-measure-1.544042?localLinksEnabled=false |title=Ohio utility chief: Energy savings hard to measure |work=Akron Beacon Journal |location=Akron |date=2014-11-25 |accessdate=2014-11-25 }}</ref>\\n\\n===Committee assignments===\\n*Energy and Natural Resources\\u2014Chair\\n*Agriculture\\n*Education\\n*Finance: General Government Subcommittee\\n*Public Utilities\\n*Transportation\\n*Workforce and Economic Development\\n*Special committee on REC and EE-Chair\\n\\n==Electoral history==\\n{|class=\\\"wikitable\\\" style=\\\"width:100%; text-align: center;\\\"\\n|-\\n! colspan=\\\"12\\\" | Election results\\n|-\\n!Year\\n!Office\\n!Election\\n!Votes for Balderson\\n!%\\n!Opponent\\n!Party\\n!Votes\\n!%\\n|-\\n|2008\\n|rowspan=2|[[Ohio House of Representatives]]\\n|General\\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |27,917\\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |54%\\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Jennifer Stewart\\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Democrat\\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |23,628\\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |46%\\n|-\\n|2010\\n|General\\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |28,236\\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |100%\\n|Unopposed\\n|\\n|\\n|\\n|-\\n|2012\\n|[[Ohio Senate]]\\n|General\\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |87,755\\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |60%\\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Teresa Scarmack\\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Democrat\\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |59,012\\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |40%\\n|}\\n\\n==References==\\n{{reflist|refs=\\n<ref name=\\\"votesmart\\\">http://votesmart.org/candidate/biography/102781/troy-balderson</ref>\\n}}\\n\\n==External links==\\n* [http://www.ohiosenate.gov/troy-balderson.html The Ohio Senate: Senator Troy Balderson (R) - District 20]\\n\\n{{Members of the Ohio Senate}}\\n\\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Balderson, Troy}}\\n[[Category:Living people]]\\n[[Category:Members of the Ohio House of Representatives]]\\n[[Category:Ohio Republicans]]\\n[[Category:Ohio State Senators]]\\n[[Category:People from Zanesville, Ohio]]\\n[[Category:1962 births]]\\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\"}]}}}}"